                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names (name of St Mary in <ref target="#p2_i1.4"/>, <ref target="#p2_i1.5"/>);
                           titles and numbers of the Psalms and Canticles; incipits and numbers of Songs; title of <ref target="#p2_i1.2"/>, <ref target="#p2_i1.3"/>and<ref target="#p2_i1.5"/> title and incipit of the daily
                           readings of <ref target="#p2_i1.4"/>; name and traditional interpretation of the Hebrew letters of Psalm 118; 
                           refrains of <ref target="#p2_i1.4"/> (occasionally abbreviated); elements of the punctuation marks and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals. A few lines (alternating with black lines) on the
                           opening page of <ref target="#p2_i1.1"/>, <ref target="#p2_i1.2"/>; two groups of lines (alternating with
                           black lines) on the incipit page of <ref target="#p2_i1.4"/>; two lines (alternating with
                           a black line) of the incipit of the daily readings of <ref target="#p2_i1.4"/>.</seg>
